    <body>
      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="875-29AI">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">The following POEM being upon a Certain D<hi rend="italics">ean</hi> who has purchased a Piece of Ground from a certain Gentleman in the Country, call'd, Sir <hi rend="italics">Arthur</hi>, and is building a fine House upon it, which he calls <hi rend="italics">Drapier's-Hall</hi>, at the the Request of the said Sir <hi rend="italics">Arthur</hi>, we are perswaded it will not be unacceptable to the Publick.</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>e give the World to understand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-2" n="2">Our thriving <hi rend="italics">Dean</hi> has purchased Land,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-3" n="3">A Purchase which will bring him clear,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-4" n="4">Above his Rent──── <hi rend="italics">Four Pound</hi> a Year?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-5" n="5">Provided to improve the Ground,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-6" n="6">He will but add <hi rend="italics">two hundred Pound</hi>;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-7" n="7">And from his endless hoarded Store,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-8" n="8">To build a House──── <hi rend="italics">Five hundred</hi> more.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-9" n="9">Sir <hi rend="italics">Arthur</hi> too, shall have his Will,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-10" n="10">And call the Mansion <hi rend="italics">DRAPIERS HILL</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-11" n="11">That when a Nation long en────d,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-12" n="12">Forgets by whom it once was saved;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-13" n="13">When none the <hi rend="italics">Draper's</hi> Praise shall sing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-14" n="14">His <hi rend="italics">Signs</hi> aloft no longer swing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-15" n="15">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-16" n="16">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-17" n="17">His <hi rend="italics">Medals</hi> and his <hi rend="italics">Prints</hi> forgotten,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-18" n="18">And all his <hi rend="italics">Handkerchiefs</hi> are rotten,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-19" n="19">His <hi rend="italics">famous Letters</hi> made waste Paper,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-20" n="20">This Hill may keep the Name of <hi rend="italics">DRAPIER</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-21" n="21">In spight of Envy flourish still,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29AI-line-22" n="22">And <hi rend="italics">Drapier's</hi> vye with <hi rend="italics">Cooper's Hill</hi>.</l>
          </lg>
